## Fix FHIR: auto-include complex datatype classes to resolve property ranges

### Context
After importing FHIR, the Ontology/Entities page logged JS warnings:
`[Map] Skipping property "address": domain="Patient" (found), range="Address" (NOT FOUND)`.
`ontology-map.js` validates that both the domain AND range class of every object
property exist in the ontology before rendering a relationship link. FHIR properties
like `Patient.address`, `Patient.name`, `CarePlan.addresses`, etc. reference complex
datatype classes (`Address`, `HumanName`, `CodeableReference`, etc.) that are not
themselves "resources" — they live outside the domain domain buckets and were
therefore excluded from the class list, causing every relationship to those types
to be silently dropped.

Fix: extend `_build_allowed_resources()` to always add `_FHIR_COMPLEX_TYPES` — the
full set of FHIR R5 compound/compound datatypes — regardless of which domain buckets
the user selected.

### Changes

1. **src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py**
   - Added `_FHIR_COMPLEX_TYPES` class-level set (30 types: Address, Age, Annotation,
     Attachment, Availability, BackboneElement, BackboneType, CodeableConcept,
     CodeableReference, Coding, ContactDetail, ContactPoint, Count, DataRequirement,
     Distance, Dosage, Duration, Element, Expression, ExtendedContactDetail,
     HumanName, Identifier, MarketingStatus, Meta, Money, Narrative,
     Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, RelatedArtifact, SampledData,
     Signature, SimpleQuantity, Timing, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, etc.)
   - `_build_allowed_resources()` now appends `_FHIR_COMPLEX_TYPES` unconditionally
   - `_BASE_HIERARCHY` in the transform pass now uses an ordered list with explicit
     parent assignments for cleaner stub injection

2. **tests/units/ontology/test_industry_importers.py**
   - Added `test_build_allowed_resources_always_includes_complex_types`: asserts
     Address, CodeableConcept, Reference, HumanName, Identifier, CodeableReference
     are present even when only FOUNDATION is selected

### Modified files
- src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py
- tests/units/ontology/test_industry_importers.py

### Test results
15/15 FHIR unit tests pass. 42/42 industry importer tests pass.

