## Fix FHIR mapper: extract attributes and relationships from OWL restrictions

### Context
After the initial import, FHIR classes appeared with no data properties and no
relationships. Root cause: FHIR's `fhir.ttl` declares ALL property bindings via
`owl:Restriction` blank nodes on classes (same BFO-style pattern as IOF), NOT via
`rdfs:domain` on the properties. The original mapper was looking for `rdfs:domain`
and finding nothing. Fix: walk `rdfs:subClassOf` blank nodes, extract
`owl:onProperty` + `owl:allValuesFrom` pairs, classify as dataProperty (FHIR
primitive type) or objectProperty (complex type), and inject into class/properties.
Also added a FHIR branch in `import_industry_ontology` to correctly resolve
ontology name and base_uri (was falling through to the IOF default).

### Changes

1. **src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py**
   - Added `_FHIR_PRIMITIVE_TYPES` class-level set of FHIR primitive datatype names
   - Added `_extract_properties_from_restrictions(graph, class_uri, class_local_name,
     known_class_names)` — walks restriction blank nodes to build data- and
     object-property lists per class
   - Rewrote `_transform_fhir_to_ontobricks()`: two-pass approach — Pass 1 collects
     classes; Pass 2 calls the restriction extractor per class; base types
     (Resource, DomainResource, BackboneElement, Element) always injected so parent
     links resolve correctly
   - `dataProperties` embedded per class (CDISC pattern); object properties returned
     flat in `properties` list

2. **src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py**
   - Added `elif kind == "fhir":` branch in `import_industry_ontology` to use
     `info["name"]` and `info["base_uri"]` (not the IOF `name`/`uri` keys)

3. **tests/units/ontology/test_industry_importers.py**
   - Updated `test_transform_returns_classes_and_properties` to assert base types
     always present (new behaviour)
   - Updated `test_transform_uses_domain_filter` to match new base-type injection
   - Added `test_transform_extracts_data_properties_from_restrictions`: builds a
     minimal graph with a Patient class + birthDate restriction and asserts the
     data property appears on the class

### Modified files
- src/back/core/industry/fhir/FhirImportService.py
- src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py
- tests/units/ontology/test_industry_importers.py

### Test results
14/14 FHIR unit tests pass. 41/41 industry importer tests pass. No regressions.

