## Fix Knowledge Graph page bottom cut off

### Context
The Sigma.js Knowledge Graph canvas and right pane were visually cut at the bottom because
`#sigmagraph-section.active` used a hardcoded `height: calc(100vh - 80px)`. The section lives
inside `.sidebar-content` which has `padding: 1rem` — the bottom padding was consuming space
not accounted for in the viewport calculation.

### Changes

1. **src/front/static/query/css/query-sigmagraph.css**
   - Added `.sidebar-content:has(#sigmagraph-section.active)` rule to strip container padding
     and set `overflow: hidden` when the graph view is active
   - Changed `#sigmagraph-section.active` from `height: calc(100vh - 80px)` to `height: 100%`
     so the section fills its container naturally
   - Added `padding: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0` on `#sigmagraph-section.active` to restore
     spacing for the section header without affecting the bottom

