## Fix: mapping-import.js crash blocking mapping designer

### Context
The mapping page threw `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'addEventListener')`
at `mapping-import.js:7`. The script's three top-level `document.getElementById(...)` calls ran
before the DOM elements were ready (or the elements live in a conditional template not yet rendered).
The null-dereference crashed the JS engine before the mapping designer initialisation chain completed,
which is why "many links were missing" — the graph simply never built.

### Changes

1. **src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-import.js**
   - Changed all three top-level `getElementById(...).addEventListener(...)` calls to
     `getElementById(...)?. addEventListener(...)` (optional chaining) so the script
     no longer crashes when the buttons are absent from the current view.

### Modified files
- src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-import.js

### Test results
No unit tests for client-side JS; crash reproduced and fixed by optional-chaining the three null-risk lookups.

