## Fix: missing inheritance (and relationship) links in mapping designer

### Context
After fixing the JS crash, many inheritance links were still absent. The root cause is that
`validNodeIds` uses an exact-string comparison (`Set.has(cls.parent)`), but the `parent` /
`domain` / `range` values stored in the ontology can differ from node IDs in two ways:

1. **Case mismatch** — e.g. node id `"FiscalYear"` vs `parent: "fiscalYear"`.
2. **Full URI stored** — e.g. `parent: "http://example.org/ontology#FiscalYear"` when
   nodes are keyed by local name only (common when the ontology was imported from OWL without
   full normalization of the `parent` field).

Neither case was handled by the existing exact lookup, so any class/property reference that
was even slightly off simply vanished from the graph.

### Changes

1. **src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js**
   - Added `resolveNodeId(id)` helper that tries three strategies in order:
     1. Exact match in `validNodeIds`
     2. Case-insensitive match via `nodeIdByLower` map
     3. URI local-part extraction (`#` or `/`) with exact + case-insensitive retry
   - Used `resolveNodeId` for both relationship links (`prop.domain` / `prop.range`)
     and inheritance links (`cls.parent`), replacing the bare `validNodeIds.has()` checks.
   - The resolved canonical node id is now used as `source`/`target` in the link object,
     so D3 can join it correctly regardless of how the reference was stored.

### Modified files
- src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js

### Test results
No regressions (display-only change; existing e2e mapping tests still pass).
